From: Petr Parkan Janda <petronijus@bastla.com>
Subject: [PATCH] brcmfmac: expose "mpc" as a module parameter

brcmf_c_preinit_dcmds() unconditionally forces the firmware "mpc"
(Minimum Power Consumption) iovar to 1, which lets the firmware power the
radio down whenever the interface is idle. The per-scan mpc toggling
(brcmf_scan_config_mpc) only runs for chips with the NEED_MPC quirk
(BCM4329), so on the BCM4330 -- and with P2P disabled -- mpc stays 1 for
the entire uptime.

On a mains-powered, always-on device (Google Nexus Q) that radio
power-down is pure harm: when traffic resumes the radio has to wake, so
bulk transfers stall and pings to the AP see 270-530 ms latency with
~30% loss, even though the signal is strong. The stock Android bcmdhd
vendor driver sets mpc=0 for exactly this reason.

Expose mpc as a module parameter (default 1, so behaviour is unchanged)
so it can be pinned to 0 via /etc/modprobe.d on mains-powered devices.

Signed-off-by: Petr Parkan Janda <petronijus@bastla.com>
---
 .../broadcom/brcm80211/brcmfmac/common.c          | 8 +++++++-
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/drivers/net/wireless/broadcom/brcm80211/brcmfmac/common.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/broadcom/brcm80211/brcmfmac/common.c
@@ -61,6 +61,11 @@ static int brcmf_roamoff;
 module_param_named(roamoff, brcmf_roamoff, int, 0400);
 MODULE_PARM_DESC(roamoff, "Do not use internal roaming engine");

+static int brcmf_mpc = 1;
+module_param_named(mpc, brcmf_mpc, int, 0400);
+MODULE_PARM_DESC(mpc,
+		 "Minimum Power Consumption: 1=radio powers down when idle (default), 0=radio always on (for mains-powered devices)");
+
 static int brcmf_iapp_enable;
 module_param_named(iapp, brcmf_iapp_enable, int, 0);
 MODULE_PARM_DESC(iapp, "Enable partial support for the obsoleted Inter-Access Point Protocol");
@@ -404,7 +409,7 @@ int brcmf_c_preinit_dcmds(struct brcmf_if *ifp)
 	}

 	/* set mpc */
-	err = brcmf_fil_iovar_int_set(ifp, "mpc", 1);
+	err = brcmf_fil_iovar_int_set(ifp, "mpc", brcmf_mpc);
 	if (err) {
 		bphy_err(drvr, "failed setting mpc\n");
 		goto done;
